---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Carl Edwards — engineering leader, architect, and builder.">
  <section class="container-prose py-20">
    <div class="text-mono-tag mb-4">// about</div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold text-ink-100 tracking-tight">
      Hi, I'm Carl.
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg mt-10 max-w-none">
      <p>
        I've been writing software since the early 1980s — starting on a Commodore 64
        with BASIC and 6502 assembly, then designing the
        <a href="https://github.com/carledwards/lcm-32">LCM-32</a>, an affordable
        single-board computer, in 1986. Forty-some years later, I'm still chasing the
        same thing: the moment a system becomes simple enough that the people using
        it can think clearly.
      </p>

      <p>
        These days I lead engineering — as a senior engineer, architect, and CTO.
        I care most about teams that ship: small enough to move, opinionated enough
        to disagree well, and wired into the work closely enough that the right
        decisions feel obvious. Most of my recent attention is on
        <strong>AI-native developer tooling</strong> — not demos, but the tools and
        workflows that change how engineers actually plan, build, and operate every day.
      </p>

      <h2>What I write about</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Engineering leadership and team design</li>
        <li>System architecture, especially the parts that age well</li>
        <li>Practical AI tooling — Claude Code, agentic workflows, observability</li>
        <li>Hardware side projects, retro computing, and the occasional weekend diversion</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/carledwards">GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://linkedin.com/in/the-carl-edwards">LinkedIn</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://twitter.com/the_CarlEdwards">Twitter / X</a></li>
        <li><a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a></li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-ink-400 text-sm mt-12">
        This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a> and
        deployed on Cloudflare Pages. Source on
        <a href="https://github.com/carledwards">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
